    "raw": "<!-- wp:html -->\n<style>\n.kk-overhaul {\n  --kk-ink:#f0f0f5; --kk-ink-2:#ffffff; --kk-muted:#a6a6b3;\n  --kk-line:rgba(255,255,255,.14); --kk-paper:rgba(255,255,255,.05); --kk-card:rgba(255,255,255,.04);\n  --kk-accent:#00e5ff; --kk-accent-soft:rgba(0,229,255,.14);\n  --kk-hot:#ff6a6a; --kk-hot-soft:rgba(255,106,106,.16);\n  --kk-r:14px; --kk-r-sm:10px;\n  --kk-sh:0 1px 2px rgba(0,0,0,.45), 0 12px 28px -14px rgba(0,0,0,.7);\n  --kk-sh-lift:0 8px 18px -6px rgba(0,0,0,.6), 0 26px 52px -18px rgba(0,0,0,.85), 0 0 0 1px rgba(0,229,255,.28);\n  color:var(--kk-ink);\n}\n/* neutralize the Aurora theme's auto drop-cap inside our content */\n.kk-overhaul p::first-letter { initial-letter:normal !important; font-size:inherit !important; font-weight:inherit !important; float:none !important; margin:0 !important; padding:0 !important; line-height:inherit !important; color:inherit !important; background:none !important; }\n.kk-overhaul a { color:var(--kk-accent); font-weight:700; text-decoration:none; }\n.kk-overhaul a:hover, .kk-overhaul a:focus-visible { text-decoration:underline; text-underline-offset:3px; }\n\n.kk-hero { padding:.4rem 0 2.2rem; border-bottom:1px solid var(--kk-line); }\n.kk-kicker { margin:0 0 .65rem; text-transform:uppercase; letter-spacing:.14em; font-size:.74rem; color:var(--kk-hot); font-weight:800; }\n.kk-display { margin:.1rem 0 1rem; font-size:2.4rem; line-height:1.08; letter-spacing:-.02em; font-weight:800; max-width:38rem; color:var(--kk-ink-2); }\n.kk-lead { font-size:1.14rem; line-height:1.62; max-width:40rem; margin:.6rem 0; color:var(--kk-ink); }\n\n.kk-actions { display:flex; flex-wrap:wrap; gap:.6rem; margin:1.4rem 0 0; }\n.kk-button { display:inline-block; padding:.7rem 1.1rem; border:2px solid var(--kk-accent); border-radius:8px; text-decoration:none !important; background:var(--kk-accent); color:#04121a !important; font-weight:700; transition:transform .15s ease, box-shadow .15s ease, background .15s ease, border-color .15s ease, color .15s ease; }\n.kk-button:hover, .kk-button:focus-visible { transform:translateY(-2px); box-shadow:var(--kk-sh-lift); }\n.kk-button.secondary { background:transparent; color:var(--kk-ink) !important; border-color:var(--kk-line); }\n.kk-button.secondary:hover, .kk-button.secondary:focus-visible { border-color:var(--kk-accent); color:var(--kk-accent) !important; }\n\n.kk-proof { display:grid; grid-template-columns:repeat(auto-fit,minmax(165px,1fr)); gap:.7rem; margin-top:1.6rem; }\n.kk-proof div { border:1px solid var(--kk-line); border-top:3px solid var(--kk-accent); border-radius:var(--kk-r-sm); padding:.95rem 1rem; background:var(--kk-card); }\n.kk-proof strong { display:block; font-size:1.02rem; line-height:1.2; letter-spacing:-.01em; color:var(--kk-ink-2); }\n.kk-proof span { display:block; color:var(--kk-muted); font-size:.9rem; margin-top:.25rem; line-height:1.45; }\n\n.kk-section { padding:2.5rem 0; border-bottom:1px solid var(--kk-line); }\n.kk-section > h2, .kk-two h2 { position:relative; padding-top:1.1rem; margin:0 0 1rem; font-size:1.62rem; line-height:1.14; letter-spacing:-.015em; font-weight:800; color:var(--kk-ink-2); }\n.kk-section > h2::before, .kk-two h2::before { content:\"\"; position:absolute; top:0; left:0; width:2.4rem; height:4px; border-radius:3px; background:var(--kk-hot); }\n.kk-section-intro { max-width:42rem; margin:0 0 1.4rem; color:var(--kk-muted); font-size:1.02rem; line-height:1.6; }\n\n.kk-grid { display:grid; grid-template-columns:repeat(auto-fit,minmax(220px,1fr)); gap:1.1rem; }\n.kk-grid:has(> :nth-child(4):last-child) { grid-template-columns:repeat(2,minmax(0,1fr)); }\n\n.kk-two { display:grid; grid-template-columns:minmax(0,1fr) minmax(220px,.75fr); gap:1.5rem; align-items:start; }\n.kk-two img { width:100%; border-radius:var(--kk-r); box-shadow:var(--kk-sh); }\n.kk-two h2 { margin-top:0; }\n\n.kk-tag { display:inline-block; background:var(--kk-hot-soft); color:var(--kk-hot); margin:0 0 .7rem; padding:.3rem .65rem; border-radius:999px; font-size:.66rem; font-weight:800; text-transform:uppercase; letter-spacing:.08em; }\n\n.kk-card { border:1px solid var(--kk-line); border-radius:var(--kk-r); background:var(--kk-card); overflow:hidden; box-shadow:var(--kk-sh); transition:transform .18s ease, box-shadow .18s ease, border-color .18s ease; }\n.kk-card:hover, .kk-card:focus-within { transform:translateY(-3px); box-shadow:var(--kk-sh-lift); border-color:rgba(0,229,255,.4); }\n.kk-card img { display:block; width:100%; aspect-ratio:4/3; object-fit:cover; background:rgba(255,255,255,.06); }\n.kk-card-body { padding:1.1rem; }\n.kk-card h3 { margin:0 0 .4rem; font-size:1.1rem; line-height:1.25; color:var(--kk-ink-2); }\n.kk-card h3 a { color:var(--kk-ink-2); }\n.kk-card p { margin:.4rem 0 0; color:var(--kk-muted); font-size:.96rem; line-height:1.5; }\n\n.kk-photo-grid { display:grid; grid-template-columns:repeat(auto-fit,minmax(210px,1fr)); gap:1.1rem; }\n\n.kk-role-card { background:var(--kk-card); border:1px solid var(--kk-line); border-top:4px solid var(--kk-accent); border-radius:var(--kk-r); padding:1.5rem 1.4rem; box-shadow:var(--kk-sh); }\n.kk-role-card h3 { margin:.15rem 0 .6rem; font-size:1.3rem; line-height:1.2; letter-spacing:-.01em; color:var(--kk-ink-2); }\n.kk-role-card h3 a { color:var(--kk-ink-2); }\n.kk-role-card p { color:var(--kk-muted); line-height:1.55; }\n.kk-role-card .kk-actions { margin-top:1.1rem; }\n.kk-role-facts { display:flex; flex-wrap:wrap; gap:.4rem; margin-top:1rem; }\n.kk-role-facts span { border:1px solid var(--kk-line); background:var(--kk-paper); border-radius:999px; padding:.3rem .65rem; font-size:.82rem; font-weight:700; color:var(--kk-ink); }\n\n.kk-pathways { display:grid; grid-template-columns:repeat(auto-fit,minmax(200px,1fr)); gap:.9rem; }\n.kk-pathways a { display:block; border:1px solid var(--kk-line); border-radius:var(--kk-r); padding:1.15rem 1.2rem; background:var(--kk-card); box-shadow:var(--kk-sh); text-decoration:none !important; transition:transform .18s ease, box-shadow .18s ease, border-color .18s ease; }\n.kk-pathways a:hover, .kk-pathways a:focus-visible { transform:translateY(-3px); box-shadow:var(--kk-sh-lift); border-color:var(--kk-accent); }\n.kk-pathways strong { display:block; font-size:1.08rem; color:var(--kk-ink-2); }\n.kk-pathways strong::after { content:\"\\2192\"; color:var(--kk-accent); margin-left:.4rem; display:inline-block; transition:transform .18s ease; }\n.kk-pathways a:hover strong::after { transform:translateX(5px); }\n.kk-pathways span { display:block; color:var(--kk-muted); font-weight:400; margin-top:.35rem; font-size:.95rem; line-height:1.5; }\n\n.kk-callout { background:var(--kk-card); border:1px solid var(--kk-line); border-radius:var(--kk-r); padding:1.3rem 1.25rem; box-shadow:var(--kk-sh); }\n.kk-callout h3 { margin:0 0 .45rem; font-size:1.12rem; color:var(--kk-ink-2); }\n.kk-callout p { margin:0; color:var(--kk-muted); line-height:1.55; }\n\n.kk-throughline { counter-reset: vals; }\n.kk-throughline .kk-callout { counter-increment: vals; background:var(--kk-paper); }\n.kk-throughline .kk-callout h3 { font-size:1.18rem; }\n.kk-throughline .kk-callout h3::before { content:counter(vals,decimal-leading-zero); display:block; font-size:1.7rem; font-weight:800; color:var(--kk-accent); letter-spacing:-.02em; margin-bottom:.35rem; font-variant-numeric:tabular-nums; }\n\n.kk-details { border:1px solid var(--kk-line); border-radius:var(--kk-r); padding:1.15rem 1.25rem; background:var(--kk-card); box-shadow:var(--kk-sh); align-self:start; transition:border-color .18s ease; }\n.kk-details[open] { border-color:var(--kk-accent); }\n.kk-details summary { cursor:pointer; font-weight:800; font-size:1.02rem; list-style:none; display:flex; align-items:center; justify-content:space-between; gap:1rem; color:var(--kk-ink-2); }\n.kk-details summary::-webkit-details-marker { display:none; }\n.kk-details summary::after { content:\"\\002B\"; color:var(--kk-accent); font-size:1.3rem; line-height:1; }\n.kk-details[open] summary::after { content:\"\\2013\"; }\n.kk-chip-cloud { display:flex; flex-wrap:wrap; gap:.4rem; margin:.9rem 0 0; }\n.kk-chip-cloud span, .kk-chip-cloud a { display:inline-block; border:1px solid var(--kk-line); background:var(--kk-paper); border-radius:999px; padding:.3rem .6rem; color:var(--kk-ink); text-decoration:none; font-size:.86rem; font-weight:600; transition:border-color .15s ease, color .15s ease, background .15s ease; }\n.kk-chip-cloud span:hover, .kk-chip-cloud a:hover { border-color:var(--kk-accent); color:var(--kk-accent); background:var(--kk-accent-soft); }\n.kk-proof-note { margin-top:1.2rem; color:var(--kk-muted); max-width:42rem; font-size:.96rem; line-height:1.55; }\n\n.kk-cta-final { border-bottom:0; }\n.kk-cta-final .kk-callout { background:var(--kk-accent-soft); border:1px solid var(--kk-accent); padding:2.1rem 1.9rem; color:var(--kk-ink); box-shadow:0 0 40px -10px rgba(0,229,255,.35); }\n.kk-cta-final .kk-callout h2 { position:relative; margin:0 0 .7rem; padding-top:1.1rem; font-size:1.7rem; line-height:1.12; letter-spacing:-.015em; font-weight:800; color:var(--kk-ink-2); }\n.kk-cta-final .kk-callout h2::before { content:\"\"; position:absolute; top:0; left:0; width:2.4rem; height:4px; border-radius:3px; background:var(--kk-hot); }\n.kk-cta-final .kk-callout p { color:var(--kk-ink); max-width:42rem; line-height:1.6; }\n.kk-cta-final .kk-actions { margin-top:1.3rem; }\n.kk-cta-final .kk-button { background:var(--kk-accent); color:#04121a !important; border-color:var(--kk-accent); }\n.kk-cta-final .kk-button.secondary { background:transparent; color:var(--kk-ink) !important; border-color:var(--kk-line); }\n.kk-cta-final .kk-button.secondary:hover { border-color:var(--kk-accent); color:var(--kk-accent) !important; }\n\n@media (max-width:760px){\n  .kk-display{ font-size:1.85rem; }\n  .kk-two{ grid-template-columns:1fr; }\n  .kk-section{ padding:2rem 0; }\n  .kk-grid:has(> :nth-child(4):last-child){ grid-template-columns:1fr; }\n}\n</style>\n\n<div class=\"kk-overhaul\">\n  <section class=\"kk-hero\">\n    <div class=\"kk-hero-grid\">\n      <div>\n        <p class=\"kk-kicker\">Podcasts, broadcast, produced interviews, panels, hosting</p>\n        <h2 class=\"kk-display\">Bring me in when your audience needs AI to sound human, useful, and alive.</h2>\n        <p class=\"kk-lead\">I am an AI keynote speaker, creative technologist, photographer, community builder, podcast guest, broadcast commentator, host, moderator, and emcee. I help audiences understand generative AI without sanding off the weird, emotional, ethical, and creative parts that make this moment matter.</p>\n        <p class=\"kk-lead\">For producers, that means a guest who can move between practical demos, big-picture stakes, sharp cultural critique, and warm human stories without turning the conversation into a press release.</p>\n        <div class=\"kk-actions\">\n          <a class=\"kk-button\" href=\"/contact/\">Book Kris for an interview</a>\n          <a class=\"kk-button secondary\" href=\"/speaking/\">See keynote work</a>\n        </div>\n      </div>\n      <figure class=\"kk-hero-photo\">\n        <img src=\"https://i0.wp.com/kriskrug.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/krug-1.webp?w=1024&amp;ssl=1\" alt=\"Kris Krug portrait for podcast producers and media bookers\" loading=\"eager\" />\n      </figure>\n    </div>\n    <ul class=\"kk-proof-strip\">\n      <li>CBC Radio Early Edition</li>\n      <li>Horizons by Compass Datacenters</li>\n      <li>Human Biography Podcast</li>\n      <li>Rachel Thexton Connects</li>\n      <li>E-ChannelNews</li>\n      <li>IndigiGenius / CBC</li>\n      <li>Kurty D Show</li>\n      <li>Teen2Life Experience</li>\n      <li>Vancouver AI Pods</li>\n      <li>Panel host / moderator</li>\n    </ul>\n  </section>\n\n  <section class=\"kk-section\">\n    <div class=\"kk-two\">\n      <div>\n        <h2>What I bring to the mic</h2>\n        <p>I can explain AI in plain language, but I am not a plain-language-only guest. The good stuff lives in the tension: creator rights, community trust, business adoption, synthetic media, public-interest AI, Indigenous data sovereignty, archive memory, weird creative tools, and the emotional reality of learning in public while the ground is moving.</p>\n        <p>I am useful in rooms that need a credible AI voice with actual field experience: building BC's AI community infrastructure, training creative and organizational teams, photographing cultural history, hosting meetups, and turning keynotes into durable public resources.</p>\n      </div>\n      <div class=\"kk-callout\">\n        <h3>Best booking formats</h3>\n        <ul>\n          <li>Podcast guest</li>\n          <li>Broadcast AI explainer</li>\n          <li>Produced video interview</li>\n          <li>Panelist or live interview guest</li>\n          <li>Moderator or fireside host</li>\n          <li>Conference emcee</li>\n          <li>Custom briefing for media or event teams</li>\n        </ul>\n      </div>\n    </div>\n  </section>\n\n  <section class=\"kk-section\">\n    <h2>Featured appearances</h2>\n    <p class=\"kk-section-intro\">A current proof stack for producers, bookers, and event teams. These are public appearances or owned pages that show range across mainstream broadcast, produced video, long-form conversation, trade media, and hosted community work.</p>\n    <div class=\"kk-grid\">\n      <article class=\"kk-card\">\n        <img src=\"https://i0.wp.com/kriskrug.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/krug-1.webp?w=1024&amp;ssl=1\" alt=\"Kris Krug media portrait\" loading=\"lazy\" />\n        <div class=\"kk-card-body\">\n          <span class=\"kk-tag\">Broadcast explainer</span>\n          <h3>CBC AI Sandbox</h3>\n          <p>Public-facing AI commentary for CBC Radio Early Edition: curious, critical, accessible, and grounded in real life.</p>\n          <p><a href=\"https://kriskrug.co/2024/07/03/new-segment-on-cbc-radio-early-edition-ai-sandbox-with-kris-krug/\">Read the CBC AI Sandbox post</a></p>\n        </div>\n      </article>\n      <article class=\"kk-card\">\n        <div class=\"kk-video\"><iframe src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/T5ANAthZewE\" title=\"Horizons interview with Kris Krug on AI models and the future of machine learning\" loading=\"lazy\" allowfullscreen></iframe></div>\n        <div class=\"kk-card-body\">\n          <span class=\"kk-tag\">Produced interview</span>\n          <h3>Horizons: Exploring AI Models</h3>\n          <p>A polished interview on AI as a human experience, daily workflows, innovation, and what changes when these tools become normal.</p>\n          <p><a href=\"https://horizons.compassdatacenters.com/series/exploring-ai-models-the-future-of-machine-learning/\">Watch the Horizons series</a></p>\n        </div>\n      </article>\n      <article class=\"kk-card\">\n        <img src=\"https://i0.wp.com/kriskrug.co/wp-content/uploads/2026/01/01k7dj5tx212rc55a76ds68rq4-Kris-Krug.png?w=1024&amp;ssl=1\" alt=\"Kris Krug BC AI member portrait\" loading=\"lazy\" />\n        <div class=\"kk-card-body\">\n          <span class=\"kk-tag\">Responsible AI</span>\n          <h3>IndigiGenius / CBC</h3>\n          <p>A public conversation with Michael Running Wolf that connects AI, Indigenous language work, sovereignty, and responsible innovation.</p>\n          <p><a href=\"https://www.indigigenius.org/media-appearances/michaelandkrisinterview\">Watch the IndigiGenius appearance</a></p>\n        </div>\n      </article>\n      <article class=\"kk-card\">\n        <img src=\"https://i0.wp.com/kriskrug.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/The20Upgrade20-20Beyond20The20Hype20-20Podcast20Artwork.jpg?w=1024&amp;ssl=1\" alt=\"Podcast artwork from Kris Krug's AI media archive\" loading=\"lazy\" />\n        <div class=\"kk-card-body\">\n          <span class=\"kk-tag\">Long-form profile</span>\n          <h3>Human Biography Podcast</h3>\n          <p>A deeper conversation with Sharad Khare about curiosity, AI, art, photography, ethics, and what it means to keep becoming.</p>\n          <p><a href=\"https://www.iheart.com/podcast/338-the-human-biography-podcas-108140410/episode/kris-krug-live-with-curiosity-256487014/\">Listen on iHeart</a></p>\n        </div>\n      </article>\n      <article class=\"kk-card\">\n        <img src=\"https://i0.wp.com/kriskrug.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/AI_Meetup_August2024_MichelleDiamond-195-scaled.jpg?w=1200&amp;ssl=1\" alt=\"Kris Krug speaking to an AI audience\" loading=\"lazy\" />\n        <div class=\"kk-card-body\">\n          <span class=\"kk-tag\">Trade media</span>\n          <h3>E-ChannelNews at ChannelNext</h3>\n          <p>AI adoption, organizational readiness, business audiences, and how technology leaders can make the shift practical.</p>\n          <p><a href=\"https://www.e-channelnews.com/interview-with-kris-krug-at-channelnext-central-2025/\">Read the E-ChannelNews interview</a></p>\n        </div>\n      </article>\n      <article class=\"kk-card\">\n        <img src=\"https://i0.wp.com/kriskrug.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/AI_Meetup_August2024_MichelleDiamond-184-scaled.jpg?w=1200&amp;ssl=1\" alt=\"Kris Krug hosting a Vancouver AI community meetup\" loading=\"lazy\" />\n        <div class=\"kk-card-body\">\n          <span class=\"kk-tag\">Hosting and community</span>\n          <h3>Vancouver AI Pods and live rooms</h3>\n          <p>Hosted community conversations, meetup stages, interviews, and public learning loops from Vancouver's AI scene.</p>\n          <p><a href=\"https://kriskrug.co/motleykrug-podcast/\">Explore the podcast archive</a></p>\n        </div>\n      </article>\n    </div>\n  </section>\n\n  <section class=\"kk-section\">\n    <h2>Conversation lanes</h2>\n    <p class=\"kk-section-intro\">The best interviews usually come from real tension. These are strong lanes for podcasts, broadcasts, panels, and live conversations.</p>\n    <div class=\"kk-lanes\">\n      <article class=\"kk-lane\">\n        <h3>AI for creatives</h3>\n        <p>What artists, filmmakers, writers, photographers, and teams actually need to know now.</p>\n      </article>\n      <article class=\"kk-lane\">\n        <h3>Responsible AI</h3>\n        <p>Governance, trust, consent, creator rights, bias, data sovereignty, and public-interest technology.</p>\n      </article>\n      <article class=\"kk-lane\">\n        <h3>BC and Vancouver's AI ecosystem</h3>\n        <p>Community infrastructure, startups, researchers, meetups, events, education, and what makes this region interesting.</p>\n      </article>\n      <article class=\"kk-lane\">\n        <h3>Human-centered tools</h3>\n        <p>How to use AI in daily workflows without losing taste, judgment, care, or a sense of authorship.</p>\n      </article>\n      <article class=\"kk-lane\">\n        <h3>Media futures</h3>\n        <p>Synthetic media, journalism, podcasts, cinematic storytelling, signal, trust, and the next shape of audience relationships.</p>\n      </article>\n      <article class=\"kk-lane\">\n        <h3>Creative community</h3>\n        <p>Open culture, internet life, digital tribes, events, archives, and how communities learn faster than institutions.</p>\n      </article>\n    </div>\n  </section>\n\n  <section class=\"kk-section\">\n    <div class=\"kk-two\">\n      <div>\n        <h2>Producer notes</h2>\n        <p><strong>Short bio:</strong> Kris Krug is a Vancouver-based AI keynote speaker, creative technologist, photographer, and community builder. He works across generative AI education, responsible technology, creative culture, and the BC AI ecosystem, helping audiences make sense of AI with more courage, taste, and humanity.</p>\n        <p><strong>Useful angles:</strong> AI without the hype cycle, what creatives should do next, the ethics of synthetic media, how communities adapt to technological change, and why human judgment gets more important as the tools get easier.</p>\n        <p><strong>Setup:</strong> I can do remote or in-person interviews, pre-recorded or live, solo guest spots, panels, firesides, broadcast explainers, hosted segments, and emcee/moderator roles.</p>\n      </div>\n      <div class=\"kk-callout\">\n        <h3>Quick links</h3>\n        <ul>\n          <li><a href=\"/contact/\">Booking contact</a></li>\n          <li><a href=\"/speaking/\">AI keynote speaker page</a></li>\n          <li><a href=\"/about/\">About Kris Krug</a></li>\n          <li><a href=\"/recent-projects-include/\">Current work</a></li>\n          <li><a href=\"https://bc-ai.ca/\">BC + AI Ecosystem</a></li>\n          <li><a href=\"https://www.bothhandsfull.com/\">Both Hands Full keynote portal</a></li>\n          <li><a href=\"https://www.punkrockai.com/\">Punk Rock AI keynote portal</a></li>\n        </ul>\n      </div>\n    </div>\n  </section>\n\n  <section class=\"kk-section\">\n    <h2>More appearances and archive links</h2>\n    <p class=\"kk-section-intro\">These links round out the media trail and help producers hear the range before booking.</p>\n    <ul class=\"kk-list\">\n      <li><a href=\"https://music.amazon.com/es-ar/podcasts/efb24614-5724-4412-a377-755e3b3ebdd4/episodes/cd1d024c-e3d4-496f-ace3-2901c89c3882/rachel-thexton-connects-03x08-kris-kr%C3%BCg-one-of-canada%27s-leading-ai-voices-talks-tech-and-tells-his-story\">Rachel Thexton Connects</a></li>\n      <li><a href=\"https://podcasts.apple.com/us/podcast/053-widen-the-lens-with-kris-krug/id1575595225?i=1000634160006\">The Kurty D Show: Widen The Lens</a></li>\n      <li><a href=\"https://music.amazon.com/es-us/podcasts/ba75295d-60de-4701-8eb6-12e17e49838a/teen2life-experience\">Teen2Life Experience</a></li>\n      <li><a href=\"https://music.amazon.com/podcasts/369594c8-9548-47ed-9dee-b61dae6c7c5a/vancouver-ai-pods\">Vancouver AI Pods</a></li>\n      <li><a href=\"https://kriskrug.co/2025/01/25/human-biography-podcast-w-sharad-khare/\">Human Biography companion post</a></li>\n      <li><a href=\"https://kriskrug.co/2024/12/17/cinematic-podcasts-hollywood-grade-storytelling-meets-generative-ai/\">Cinematic Podcasts essay</a></li>\n    </ul>\n  </section>\n\n  <section class=\"kk-section\">\n    <div class=\"kk-callout\">\n      <h2>Book Kris for a podcast, broadcast segment, panel, or hosted event</h2>\n      <p>I can join as a podcast guest, AI commentator, panelist, live interview guest, moderator, host, emcee, keynote speaker, or workshop lead. Tell me the audience, format, timeline, and the tension you want the conversation to hold.</p>\n      <div class=\"kk-actions\">\n        <a class=\"kk-button\" href=\"/contact/\">Start a booking conversation</a>\n        <a class=\"kk-button secondary\" href=\"/speaking/\">Explore keynote topics</a>\n      </div>\n      <p class=\"kk-mini\">This page uses public source links and owned-site media only. No private booking notes, travel details, or personal contact details are included here.</p>\n    </div>\n  </section>\n</div>\n<!-- /wp:html -->\n",
    "rendered": "\n<style>\n.kk-overhaul {\n  --kk-ink:#f0f0f5; --kk-ink-2:#ffffff; --kk-muted:#a6a6b3;\n  --kk-line:rgba(255,255,255,.14); --kk-paper:rgba(255,255,255,.05); --kk-card:rgba(255,255,255,.04);\n  --kk-accent:#00e5ff; --kk-accent-soft:rgba(0,229,255,.14);\n  --kk-hot:#ff6a6a; --kk-hot-soft:rgba(255,106,106,.16);\n  --kk-r:14px; --kk-r-sm:10px;\n  --kk-sh:0 1px 2px rgba(0,0,0,.45), 0 12px 28px -14px rgba(0,0,0,.7);\n  --kk-sh-lift:0 8px 18px -6px rgba(0,0,0,.6), 0 26px 52px -18px rgba(0,0,0,.85), 0 0 0 1px rgba(0,229,255,.28);\n  color:var(--kk-ink);\n}\n/* neutralize the Aurora theme's auto drop-cap inside our content */\n.kk-overhaul p::first-letter { initial-letter:normal !important; font-size:inherit !important; font-weight:inherit !important; float:none !important; margin:0 !important; padding:0 !important; line-height:inherit !important; color:inherit !important; background:none !important; }\n.kk-overhaul a { color:var(--kk-accent); font-weight:700; text-decoration:none; }\n.kk-overhaul a:hover, .kk-overhaul a:focus-visible { text-decoration:underline; text-underline-offset:3px; }\n\n.kk-hero { padding:.4rem 0 2.2rem; border-bottom:1px solid var(--kk-line); }\n.kk-kicker { margin:0 0 .65rem; text-transform:uppercase; letter-spacing:.14em; font-size:.74rem; color:var(--kk-hot); font-weight:800; }\n.kk-display { margin:.1rem 0 1rem; font-size:2.4rem; line-height:1.08; letter-spacing:-.02em; font-weight:800; max-width:38rem; color:var(--kk-ink-2); }\n.kk-lead { font-size:1.14rem; line-height:1.62; max-width:40rem; margin:.6rem 0; color:var(--kk-ink); }\n\n.kk-actions { display:flex; flex-wrap:wrap; gap:.6rem; margin:1.4rem 0 0; }\n.kk-button { display:inline-block; padding:.7rem 1.1rem; border:2px solid var(--kk-accent); border-radius:8px; text-decoration:none !important; background:var(--kk-accent); color:#04121a !important; font-weight:700; transition:transform .15s ease, box-shadow .15s ease, background .15s ease, border-color .15s ease, color .15s ease; }\n.kk-button:hover, .kk-button:focus-visible { transform:translateY(-2px); box-shadow:var(--kk-sh-lift); }\n.kk-button.secondary { background:transparent; color:var(--kk-ink) !important; border-color:var(--kk-line); }\n.kk-button.secondary:hover, .kk-button.secondary:focus-visible { border-color:var(--kk-accent); color:var(--kk-accent) !important; }\n\n.kk-proof { display:grid; grid-template-columns:repeat(auto-fit,minmax(165px,1fr)); gap:.7rem; margin-top:1.6rem; }\n.kk-proof div { border:1px solid var(--kk-line); border-top:3px solid var(--kk-accent); border-radius:var(--kk-r-sm); padding:.95rem 1rem; background:var(--kk-card); }\n.kk-proof strong { display:block; font-size:1.02rem; line-height:1.2; letter-spacing:-.01em; color:var(--kk-ink-2); }\n.kk-proof span { display:block; color:var(--kk-muted); font-size:.9rem; margin-top:.25rem; line-height:1.45; }\n\n.kk-section { padding:2.5rem 0; border-bottom:1px solid var(--kk-line); }\n.kk-section > h2, .kk-two h2 { position:relative; padding-top:1.1rem; margin:0 0 1rem; font-size:1.62rem; line-height:1.14; letter-spacing:-.015em; font-weight:800; color:var(--kk-ink-2); }\n.kk-section > h2::before, .kk-two h2::before { content:\"\"; position:absolute; top:0; left:0; width:2.4rem; height:4px; border-radius:3px; background:var(--kk-hot); }\n.kk-section-intro { max-width:42rem; margin:0 0 1.4rem; color:var(--kk-muted); font-size:1.02rem; line-height:1.6; }\n\n.kk-grid { display:grid; grid-template-columns:repeat(auto-fit,minmax(220px,1fr)); gap:1.1rem; }\n.kk-grid:has(> :nth-child(4):last-child) { grid-template-columns:repeat(2,minmax(0,1fr)); }\n\n.kk-two { display:grid; grid-template-columns:minmax(0,1fr) minmax(220px,.75fr); gap:1.5rem; align-items:start; }\n.kk-two img { width:100%; border-radius:var(--kk-r); box-shadow:var(--kk-sh); }\n.kk-two h2 { margin-top:0; }\n\n.kk-tag { display:inline-block; background:var(--kk-hot-soft); color:var(--kk-hot); margin:0 0 .7rem; padding:.3rem .65rem; border-radius:999px; font-size:.66rem; font-weight:800; text-transform:uppercase; letter-spacing:.08em; }\n\n.kk-card { border:1px solid var(--kk-line); border-radius:var(--kk-r); background:var(--kk-card); overflow:hidden; box-shadow:var(--kk-sh); transition:transform .18s ease, box-shadow .18s ease, border-color .18s ease; }\n.kk-card:hover, .kk-card:focus-within { transform:translateY(-3px); box-shadow:var(--kk-sh-lift); border-color:rgba(0,229,255,.4); }\n.kk-card img { display:block; width:100%; aspect-ratio:4/3; object-fit:cover; background:rgba(255,255,255,.06); }\n.kk-card-body { padding:1.1rem; }\n.kk-card h3 { margin:0 0 .4rem; font-size:1.1rem; line-height:1.25; color:var(--kk-ink-2); }\n.kk-card h3 a { color:var(--kk-ink-2); }\n.kk-card p { margin:.4rem 0 0; color:var(--kk-muted); font-size:.96rem; line-height:1.5; }\n\n.kk-photo-grid { display:grid; grid-template-columns:repeat(auto-fit,minmax(210px,1fr)); gap:1.1rem; }\n\n.kk-role-card { background:var(--kk-card); border:1px solid var(--kk-line); border-top:4px solid var(--kk-accent); border-radius:var(--kk-r); padding:1.5rem 1.4rem; box-shadow:var(--kk-sh); }\n.kk-role-card h3 { margin:.15rem 0 .6rem; font-size:1.3rem; line-height:1.2; letter-spacing:-.01em; color:var(--kk-ink-2); }\n.kk-role-card h3 a { color:var(--kk-ink-2); }\n.kk-role-card p { color:var(--kk-muted); line-height:1.55; }\n.kk-role-card .kk-actions { margin-top:1.1rem; }\n.kk-role-facts { display:flex; flex-wrap:wrap; gap:.4rem; margin-top:1rem; }\n.kk-role-facts span { border:1px solid var(--kk-line); background:var(--kk-paper); border-radius:999px; padding:.3rem .65rem; font-size:.82rem; font-weight:700; color:var(--kk-ink); }\n\n.kk-pathways { display:grid; grid-template-columns:repeat(auto-fit,minmax(200px,1fr)); gap:.9rem; }\n.kk-pathways a { display:block; border:1px solid var(--kk-line); border-radius:var(--kk-r); padding:1.15rem 1.2rem; background:var(--kk-card); box-shadow:var(--kk-sh); text-decoration:none !important; transition:transform .18s ease, box-shadow .18s ease, border-color .18s ease; }\n.kk-pathways a:hover, .kk-pathways a:focus-visible { transform:translateY(-3px); box-shadow:var(--kk-sh-lift); border-color:var(--kk-accent); }\n.kk-pathways strong { display:block; font-size:1.08rem; color:var(--kk-ink-2); }\n.kk-pathways strong::after { content:\"\\2192\"; color:var(--kk-accent); margin-left:.4rem; display:inline-block; transition:transform .18s ease; }\n.kk-pathways a:hover strong::after { transform:translateX(5px); }\n.kk-pathways span { display:block; color:var(--kk-muted); font-weight:400; margin-top:.35rem; font-size:.95rem; line-height:1.5; }\n\n.kk-callout { background:var(--kk-card); border:1px solid var(--kk-line); border-radius:var(--kk-r); padding:1.3rem 1.25rem; box-shadow:var(--kk-sh); }\n.kk-callout h3 { margin:0 0 .45rem; font-size:1.12rem; color:var(--kk-ink-2); }\n.kk-callout p { margin:0; color:var(--kk-muted); line-height:1.55; }\n\n.kk-throughline { counter-reset: vals; }\n.kk-throughline .kk-callout { counter-increment: vals; background:var(--kk-paper); }\n.kk-throughline .kk-callout h3 { font-size:1.18rem; }\n.kk-throughline .kk-callout h3::before { content:counter(vals,decimal-leading-zero); display:block; font-size:1.7rem; font-weight:800; color:var(--kk-accent); letter-spacing:-.02em; margin-bottom:.35rem; font-variant-numeric:tabular-nums; }\n\n.kk-details { border:1px solid var(--kk-line); border-radius:var(--kk-r); padding:1.15rem 1.25rem; background:var(--kk-card); box-shadow:var(--kk-sh); align-self:start; transition:border-color .18s ease; }\n.kk-details[open] { border-color:var(--kk-accent); }\n.kk-details summary { cursor:pointer; font-weight:800; font-size:1.02rem; list-style:none; display:flex; align-items:center; justify-content:space-between; gap:1rem; color:var(--kk-ink-2); }\n.kk-details summary::-webkit-details-marker { display:none; }\n.kk-details summary::after { content:\"\\002B\"; color:var(--kk-accent); font-size:1.3rem; line-height:1; }\n.kk-details[open] summary::after { content:\"\\2013\"; }\n.kk-chip-cloud { display:flex; flex-wrap:wrap; gap:.4rem; margin:.9rem 0 0; }\n.kk-chip-cloud span, .kk-chip-cloud a { display:inline-block; border:1px solid var(--kk-line); background:var(--kk-paper); border-radius:999px; padding:.3rem .6rem; color:var(--kk-ink); text-decoration:none; font-size:.86rem; font-weight:600; transition:border-color .15s ease, color .15s ease, background .15s ease; }\n.kk-chip-cloud span:hover, .kk-chip-cloud a:hover { border-color:var(--kk-accent); color:var(--kk-accent); background:var(--kk-accent-soft); }\n.kk-proof-note { margin-top:1.2rem; color:var(--kk-muted); max-width:42rem; font-size:.96rem; line-height:1.55; }\n\n.kk-cta-final { border-bottom:0; }\n.kk-cta-final .kk-callout { background:var(--kk-accent-soft); border:1px solid var(--kk-accent); padding:2.1rem 1.9rem; color:var(--kk-ink); box-shadow:0 0 40px -10px rgba(0,229,255,.35); }\n.kk-cta-final .kk-callout h2 { position:relative; margin:0 0 .7rem; padding-top:1.1rem; font-size:1.7rem; line-height:1.12; letter-spacing:-.015em; font-weight:800; color:var(--kk-ink-2); }\n.kk-cta-final .kk-callout h2::before { content:\"\"; position:absolute; top:0; left:0; width:2.4rem; height:4px; border-radius:3px; background:var(--kk-hot); }\n.kk-cta-final .kk-callout p { color:var(--kk-ink); max-width:42rem; line-height:1.6; }\n.kk-cta-final .kk-actions { margin-top:1.3rem; }\n.kk-cta-final .kk-button { background:var(--kk-accent); color:#04121a !important; border-color:var(--kk-accent); }\n.kk-cta-final .kk-button.secondary { background:transparent; color:var(--kk-ink) !important; border-color:var(--kk-line); }\n.kk-cta-final .kk-button.secondary:hover { border-color:var(--kk-accent); color:var(--kk-accent) !important; }\n\n@media (max-width:760px){\n  .kk-display{ font-size:1.85rem; }\n  .kk-two{ grid-template-columns:1fr; }\n  .kk-section{ padding:2rem 0; }\n  .kk-grid:has(> :nth-child(4):last-child){ grid-template-columns:1fr; }\n}\n</style>\n\n<div class=\"kk-overhaul\">\n  <section class=\"kk-hero\">\n    <div class=\"kk-hero-grid\">\n      <div>\n        <p class=\"kk-kicker\">Podcasts, broadcast, produced interviews, panels, hosting</p>\n        <h2 class=\"kk-display\">Bring me in when your audience needs AI to sound human, useful, and alive.</h2>\n        <p class=\"kk-lead\">I am an AI keynote speaker, creative technologist, photographer, community builder, podcast guest, broadcast commentator, host, moderator, and emcee. I help audiences understand generative AI without sanding off the weird, emotional, ethical, and creative parts that make this moment matter.</p>\n        <p class=\"kk-lead\">For producers, that means a guest who can move between practical demos, big-picture stakes, sharp cultural critique, and warm human stories without turning the conversation into a press release.</p>\n        <div class=\"kk-actions\">\n          <a class=\"kk-button\" href=\"/contact/\">Book Kris for an interview</a>\n          <a class=\"kk-button secondary\" href=\"/speaking/\">See keynote work</a>\n        </div>\n      </div>\n      <figure class=\"kk-hero-photo\">\n        <img decoding=\"async\" src=\"https://i0.wp.com/kriskrug.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/krug-1.webp?w=1024&amp;ssl=1\" alt=\"Kris Krug portrait for podcast producers and media bookers\" loading=\"eager\" />\n      </figure>\n    </div>\n    <ul class=\"kk-proof-strip\">\n      <li>CBC Radio Early Edition</li>\n      <li>Horizons by Compass Datacenters</li>\n      <li>Human Biography Podcast</li>\n      <li>Rachel Thexton Connects</li>\n      <li>E-ChannelNews</li>\n      <li>IndigiGenius / CBC</li>\n      <li>Kurty D Show</li>\n      <li>Teen2Life Experience</li>\n      <li>Vancouver AI Pods</li>\n      <li>Panel host / moderator</li>\n    </ul>\n  </section>\n\n  <section class=\"kk-section\">\n    <div class=\"kk-two\">\n      <div>\n        <h2>What I bring to the mic</h2>\n        <p>I can explain AI in plain language, but I am not a plain-language-only guest. The good stuff lives in the tension: creator rights, community trust, business adoption, synthetic media, public-interest AI, Indigenous data sovereignty, archive memory, weird creative tools, and the emotional reality of learning in public while the ground is moving.</p>\n        <p>I am useful in rooms that need a credible AI voice with actual field experience: building BC&#8217;s AI community infrastructure, training creative and organizational teams, photographing cultural history, hosting meetups, and turning keynotes into durable public resources.</p>\n      </div>\n      <div class=\"kk-callout\">\n        <h3>Best booking formats</h3>\n        <ul>\n          <li>Podcast guest</li>\n          <li>Broadcast AI explainer</li>\n          <li>Produced video interview</li>\n          <li>Panelist or live interview guest</li>\n          <li>Moderator or fireside host</li>\n          <li>Conference emcee</li>\n          <li>Custom briefing for media or event teams</li>\n        </ul>\n      </div>\n    </div>\n  </section>\n\n  <section class=\"kk-section\">\n    <h2>Featured appearances</h2>\n    <p class=\"kk-section-intro\">A current proof stack for producers, bookers, and event teams. These are public appearances or owned pages that show range across mainstream broadcast, produced video, long-form conversation, trade media, and hosted community work.</p>\n    <div class=\"kk-grid\">\n      <article class=\"kk-card\">\n        <img decoding=\"async\" src=\"https://i0.wp.com/kriskrug.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/03/krug-1.webp?w=1024&amp;ssl=1\" alt=\"Kris Krug media portrait\" loading=\"lazy\" />\n        <div class=\"kk-card-body\">\n          <span class=\"kk-tag\">Broadcast explainer</span>\n          <h3>CBC AI Sandbox</h3>\n          <p>Public-facing AI commentary for CBC Radio Early Edition: curious, critical, accessible, and grounded in real life.</p>\n          <p><a href=\"https://kriskrug.co/2024/07/03/new-segment-on-cbc-radio-early-edition-ai-sandbox-with-kris-krug/\">Read the CBC AI Sandbox post</a></p>\n        </div>\n      </article>\n      <article class=\"kk-card\">\n        <div class=\"kk-video\"><iframe src=\"https://www.youtube.com/embed/T5ANAthZewE\" title=\"Horizons interview with Kris Krug on AI models and the future of machine learning\" loading=\"lazy\" allowfullscreen></iframe></div>\n        <div class=\"kk-card-body\">\n          <span class=\"kk-tag\">Produced interview</span>\n          <h3>Horizons: Exploring AI Models</h3>\n          <p>A polished interview on AI as a human experience, daily workflows, innovation, and what changes when these tools become normal.</p>\n          <p><a href=\"https://horizons.compassdatacenters.com/series/exploring-ai-models-the-future-of-machine-learning/\">Watch the Horizons series</a></p>\n        </div>\n      </article>\n      <article class=\"kk-card\">\n        <img decoding=\"async\" src=\"https://i0.wp.com/kriskrug.co/wp-content/uploads/2026/01/01k7dj5tx212rc55a76ds68rq4-Kris-Krug.png?w=1024&amp;ssl=1\" alt=\"Kris Krug BC AI member portrait\" loading=\"lazy\" />\n        <div class=\"kk-card-body\">\n          <span class=\"kk-tag\">Responsible AI</span>\n          <h3>IndigiGenius / CBC</h3>\n          <p>A public conversation with Michael Running Wolf that connects AI, Indigenous language work, sovereignty, and responsible innovation.</p>\n          <p><a href=\"https://www.indigigenius.org/media-appearances/michaelandkrisinterview\">Watch the IndigiGenius appearance</a></p>\n        </div>\n      </article>\n      <article class=\"kk-card\">\n        <img decoding=\"async\" src=\"https://i0.wp.com/kriskrug.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/The20Upgrade20-20Beyond20The20Hype20-20Podcast20Artwork.jpg?w=1024&amp;ssl=1\" alt=\"Podcast artwork from Kris Krug's AI media archive\" loading=\"lazy\" />\n        <div class=\"kk-card-body\">\n          <span class=\"kk-tag\">Long-form profile</span>\n          <h3>Human Biography Podcast</h3>\n          <p>A deeper conversation with Sharad Khare about curiosity, AI, art, photography, ethics, and what it means to keep becoming.</p>\n          <p><a href=\"https://www.iheart.com/podcast/338-the-human-biography-podcas-108140410/episode/kris-krug-live-with-curiosity-256487014/\">Listen on iHeart</a></p>\n        </div>\n      </article>\n      <article class=\"kk-card\">\n        <img decoding=\"async\" src=\"https://i0.wp.com/kriskrug.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/AI_Meetup_August2024_MichelleDiamond-195-scaled.jpg?w=1200&amp;ssl=1\" alt=\"Kris Krug speaking to an AI audience\" loading=\"lazy\" />\n        <div class=\"kk-card-body\">\n          <span class=\"kk-tag\">Trade media</span>\n          <h3>E-ChannelNews at ChannelNext</h3>\n          <p>AI adoption, organizational readiness, business audiences, and how technology leaders can make the shift practical.</p>\n          <p><a href=\"https://www.e-channelnews.com/interview-with-kris-krug-at-channelnext-central-2025/\">Read the E-ChannelNews interview</a></p>\n        </div>\n      </article>\n      <article class=\"kk-card\">\n        <img decoding=\"async\" src=\"https://i0.wp.com/kriskrug.co/wp-content/uploads/2024/09/AI_Meetup_August2024_MichelleDiamond-184-scaled.jpg?w=1200&amp;ssl=1\" alt=\"Kris Krug hosting a Vancouver AI community meetup\" loading=\"lazy\" />\n        <div class=\"kk-card-body\">\n          <span class=\"kk-tag\">Hosting and community</span>\n          <h3>Vancouver AI Pods and live rooms</h3>\n          <p>Hosted community conversations, meetup stages, interviews, and public learning loops from Vancouver&#8217;s AI scene.</p>\n          <p><a href=\"https://kriskrug.co/motleykrug-podcast/\">Explore the podcast archive</a></p>\n        </div>\n      </article>\n    </div>\n  </section>\n\n  <section class=\"kk-section\">\n    <h2>Conversation lanes</h2>\n    <p class=\"kk-section-intro\">The best interviews usually come from real tension. These are strong lanes for podcasts, broadcasts, panels, and live conversations.</p>\n    <div class=\"kk-lanes\">\n      <article class=\"kk-lane\">\n        <h3>AI for creatives</h3>\n        <p>What artists, filmmakers, writers, photographers, and teams actually need to know now.</p>\n      </article>\n      <article class=\"kk-lane\">\n        <h3>Responsible AI</h3>\n        <p>Governance, trust, consent, creator rights, bias, data sovereignty, and public-interest technology.</p>\n      </article>\n      <article class=\"kk-lane\">\n        <h3>BC and Vancouver&#8217;s AI ecosystem</h3>\n        <p>Community infrastructure, startups, researchers, meetups, events, education, and what makes this region interesting.</p>\n      </article>\n      <article class=\"kk-lane\">\n        <h3>Human-centered tools</h3>\n        <p>How to use AI in daily workflows without losing taste, judgment, care, or a sense of authorship.</p>\n      </article>\n      <article class=\"kk-lane\">\n        <h3>Media futures</h3>\n        <p>Synthetic media, journalism, podcasts, cinematic storytelling, signal, trust, and the next shape of audience relationships.</p>\n      </article>\n      <article class=\"kk-lane\">\n        <h3>Creative community</h3>\n        <p>Open culture, internet life, digital tribes, events, archives, and how communities learn faster than institutions.</p>\n      </article>\n    </div>\n  </section>\n\n  <section class=\"kk-section\">\n    <div class=\"kk-two\">\n      <div>\n        <h2>Producer notes</h2>\n        <p><strong>Short bio:</strong> Kris Krug is a Vancouver-based AI keynote speaker, creative technologist, photographer, and community builder. He works across generative AI education, responsible technology, creative culture, and the BC AI ecosystem, helping audiences make sense of AI with more courage, taste, and humanity.</p>\n        <p><strong>Useful angles:</strong> AI without the hype cycle, what creatives should do next, the ethics of synthetic media, how communities adapt to technological change, and why human judgment gets more important as the tools get easier.</p>\n        <p><strong>Setup:</strong> I can do remote or in-person interviews, pre-recorded or live, solo guest spots, panels, firesides, broadcast explainers, hosted segments, and emcee/moderator roles.</p>\n      </div>\n      <div class=\"kk-callout\">\n        <h3>Quick links</h3>\n        <ul>\n          <li><a href=\"/contact/\">Booking contact</a></li>\n          <li><a href=\"/speaking/\">AI keynote speaker page</a></li>\n          <li><a href=\"/about/\">About Kris Krug</a></li>\n          <li><a href=\"/recent-projects-include/\">Current work</a></li>\n          <li><a href=\"https://bc-ai.ca/\">BC + AI Ecosystem</a></li>\n          <li><a href=\"https://www.bothhandsfull.com/\">Both Hands Full keynote portal</a></li>\n          <li><a href=\"https://www.punkrockai.com/\">Punk Rock AI keynote portal</a></li>\n        </ul>\n      </div>\n    </div>\n  </section>\n\n  <section class=\"kk-section\">\n    <h2>More appearances and archive links</h2>\n    <p class=\"kk-section-intro\">These links round out the media trail and help producers hear the range before booking.</p>\n    <ul class=\"kk-list\">\n      <li><a href=\"https://music.amazon.com/es-ar/podcasts/efb24614-5724-4412-a377-755e3b3ebdd4/episodes/cd1d024c-e3d4-496f-ace3-2901c89c3882/rachel-thexton-connects-03x08-kris-kr%C3%BCg-one-of-canada%27s-leading-ai-voices-talks-tech-and-tells-his-story\">Rachel Thexton Connects</a></li>\n      <li><a href=\"https://podcasts.apple.com/us/podcast/053-widen-the-lens-with-kris-krug/id1575595225?i=1000634160006\">The Kurty D Show: Widen The Lens</a></li>\n      <li><a href=\"https://music.amazon.com/es-us/podcasts/ba75295d-60de-4701-8eb6-12e17e49838a/teen2life-experience\">Teen2Life Experience</a></li>\n      <li><a href=\"https://music.amazon.com/podcasts/369594c8-9548-47ed-9dee-b61dae6c7c5a/vancouver-ai-pods\">Vancouver AI Pods</a></li>\n      <li><a href=\"https://kriskrug.co/2025/01/25/human-biography-podcast-w-sharad-khare/\">Human Biography companion post</a></li>\n      <li><a href=\"https://kriskrug.co/2024/12/17/cinematic-podcasts-hollywood-grade-storytelling-meets-generative-ai/\">Cinematic Podcasts essay</a></li>\n    </ul>\n  </section>\n\n  <section class=\"kk-section\">\n    <div class=\"kk-callout\">\n      <h2>Book Kris for a podcast, broadcast segment, panel, or hosted event</h2>\n      <p>I can join as a podcast guest, AI commentator, panelist, live interview guest, moderator, host, emcee, keynote speaker, or workshop lead. Tell me the audience, format, timeline, and the tension you want the conversation to hold.</p>\n      <div class=\"kk-actions\">\n        <a class=\"kk-button\" href=\"/contact/\">Start a booking conversation</a>\n        <a class=\"kk-button secondary\" href=\"/speaking/\">Explore keynote topics</a>\n      </div>\n      <p class=\"kk-mini\">This page uses public source links and owned-site media only. No private booking notes, travel details, or personal contact details are included here.</p>\n    </div>\n  </section>\n</div>\n\n",
